p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049455" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670260049455"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Versatile&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192257752" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673192257752" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>By combining an elliptical and stationary bike into 1 machine, an elliptical bike combo offers a range of versatile workout options.</p><p>With most elliptical combos, youâ€™re able to slide the seat forward, so it can be used as a stationary bike, and slide it fully back for elliptical mode. Some combos also offer a recumbent bike mode, making it a 3-in-1 combo machine.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670260049451" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670260049451" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673204739092" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673204739092"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Value for Money</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049456" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670260049456" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><div>Even with two cardio machines built into one, elliptical bike combos donâ€™t cost much more than a normal cardio machine.</div><div><br></div><div>This means that when buying a combo machine, you can save the amount of money one of the machines would cost, making them an excellent budget option.</div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1671120057351" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1671120057351"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Space-Saving</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670260049460" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670260049460"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Unless you have a huge house, home gym space usually plays a role in choosing the right equipment. Whilst elliptical bike combos are larger than each machine on its own, they still help you to save a lot of space if you combine both together.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670780526876" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1670780526876" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/dbc85720-e9db-4887-9909-072d88bfc9b6/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-training-on-elliptical-and-bike-combo-at-gym.png" alt="athlete training on elliptical and bike combo" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192374669" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673192374669"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Joint-Friendly&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673192394930" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673192394930"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>One of the main benefits of using an elliptical is that it allows joint-friendly training. Joint issues or impairments can be one of the main barriers to not exercising or doing a bad workout.</p><p><br></p><p>By using your arms and legs to power the machine, you never place your feet on the ground, meaning there is little to no impact. This makes them ideal for rehabilitation, injury prevention, or for older populations with increased risk of <a href="https